{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nYou are implementing a task for the ishi project (a Rust TUI app for Linear).\n\n## Your task\nLinear issue: JEM-86 — Open Linear (o+l) — open selected issue in Linear\n\n## Instructions\n1. Fetch the full description of Linear issue JEM-86 (team 'JEM') and read it carefully.\n2. Set the issue state to 'In Progress'.\n3. Read the existing codebase to understand conventions, structure and patterns.\n4. Implement the feature or fix described in the issue.\n5. Write thorough tests for your changes.\n6. Run the full test suite with 'cargo test' and fix any failures until all tests pass.\n7. Run 'cargo clippy' and fix any warnings.\n8. If you discover additional work needed (bugs, missing features, TODOs), create new Linear issues in team 'JEM' project 'Ishi' for each.\n9. When implementation is complete and all tests pass:\n   a. Run: jj describe -m '[JEM-86] Open Linear (o+l) — open selected issue in Linear'\n   b. Run: jj git push\n   c. Run: jj new\n10. Set the Linear issue JEM-86 state to 'Done'.\n11. Print a brief summary of what you implemented.\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"T-019cff71-c993-74f3-bc85-44bb4a8742c5"}
